passages.text: FY25 Result: Solid result and capital returns, retain Neutral

Key takeaways from the FY25 result: 1) EBITDA/NPAT were beats vs consensus but in line with JPMc, 2) net debt of US \(749m was in line and no changes have been made to guidance, and 3) capital management remains key to the PRU investment case, with the 5Acps final dividend taking FY25 dividend to 7.5cps, which was a \(19\%\) beat to both JPMc/Cons, and a \(\) 100m\(top up of the existing buyback authorised. Our PT falls to\) \ \(3.70 / s h\) after incorporating share buybacks and we retain our Neutral rating.

- EBITDA/NPAT beat and strong capital returns continue. EBITDA came in line with JPMc but was a \(2\%\) beat to consensus. NPAT of US \(422m was also within JPMc but a \(14\%\) beat to consensus. Net debt of US \(749m matched JPMc and consensus. The final dividend of 5cps was announced taking the full year div to 7.5cps, a \(19\%\) beat to both JPMc and Consensus. The buyback was topped up by\) \ \(100m\) with A \(83.6m of the original\) \ \(100m\) complete.

- PT \(\) 3.70/sh\(; retain Neutral. Our FY26 earnings are largely unchanged post the result on unchanged guidance. Our PT falls to\) \ \(3.70\) after updating our model for share buybacks which have impacted the share count. We retain our Neutral rating. While the capital returns story for PRU remains strong, upcoming newsflow around Tanzania and Cote D'Ivoire elections in October keeps headline risk at front of mind. We see better value elsewhere in the mid-cap gold space with RRL and GMD our preferred picks.

Perseus Mining operates three gold mines in West Africa: the Edikan Gold Mine (EGM, or Edikan) in the Republic of Ghana; the Sissingué Gold Mine (SGM, or Sissingué); and the Yaouré Gold Mine (YGM, or Yaouré), both in the Republic of Côte d'Ivoire. In addition to its gold mining activities, the Group conducts mineral exploration and evaluation and project development activities in Africa, including the Nyanzaga development project in Tanzania, the Meyas Sands project in Sudan, and a \(17.98\%\) equity stake in ASX- listed Predictive Discovery (PDI.ASX), which owns the Bankan development project in Guinea. We are Neutral, based on valuation.
Our Jun- 26 price target is based on a blended DCF \((50\%)\) and EV/EBITDA multiple \((50\%)\) valuations, rounded to the nearest 10cps. We use a WACC of \(17.9\%\) .
